  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [ ] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (15204ec 2022-11-29T00:04:59.199031Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge fmt\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n`forge init` a new project and update `setNumber` like so:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction setNumber(uint256 newNumber) public {\r\n    number =   newNumber; // forgefmt: disable-line\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter running `forge fmt` it becomes:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction setNumber(uint256 newNumber) public {\r\n    number =   newNumber;// forgefmt: disable-line\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that the functionality still works, it's just the leading space before `//` that is removed. Additionally, the extra spaces between the equals sign and `newNumber` are not removed",
